Theme for web: Indie videogame style
Colour: Dark theme with 8 bit Colour
Webname: Gamerdiary
Web application type: One page

Buttons: 
Login -> Open a window with email, password, and button enter -> Log in
Registration -> Open a  window with Email, Password, User name, Terms, button enter -> Window Registration successful, please Login
Search -> When user enter text, appear list with games with similar name, clickable -> Open Game Page in lowest part of the screen
Game Library -> Open Game library section under
Pick a random game -> Open random game page under 
Upcoming -> Open Upcoming Games section
<- near buttons Game Library, Pick a random game, Upcoming means  go back within web application
- > near buttons Game Library, Pick a random game, Upcoming means go forward within web application
Game -> Game window when clicked changes to the game page
Main Page -> Open main page under
Profile -> Open under profile page
Avatar -> Picture added by users for profile
Game in list -> Show how many games player have inside their list
Favorite game -> Show the game logo whitch player chose as favourite
Game logo -> Logo of the game created by administrator
Add to list -> By pressing user add game to list (basic status on-hold)
Make a favourite -> Add game to profile as favourite (only one game can be favourite)
Status -> Four status: Played, Want to play, On hold, Dropped (Drop-down list)
Score -> 1 to 10 (Drop-down list)
Youtube Trailer -> embedded video from YouTube
Description -> game description written by administrator
Genre -> Genre of the game shoter/arpg etc.
Change avatar -> Button that give opportunity to add new avatar for user
New password -> Input field for user for password changing
Confirm new password -> Must be the same as new password, for double cheking that user dont make a mistake -> enter must be pressed to apply the changes
New Username ->  Input field for user for username changing -> enter must be pressed to apply the changes
Line Played, Want to play, On hold, Dropped -> All 4 are clickable, this is a filter that displays games depending on the user's status

